{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2c514f26-7fbf-4d9f-b51c-05c6b5d55c3a","content":"\n\nUse `Assert.ThrowsException` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName);\n}\n```\n\n**Why migrate:**\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if *any* line throws, masking bugs\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` pins the exact call and lets you inspect the exception (message, properties, inner exception)\n- The test fails properly if no exception is thrown","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ce7a77d7-be25-49de-b4db-28b52f076dba","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question - no tools needed.","outputTokens":233},"id":"bd959205-c25d-4e25-bbbd-941d7f5328b5","timestamp":"2026-04-03T03:15:46.575Z","parentId":"c2c020eb-51b9-46a8-a06b-e6850060dae2"}
